losed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 6, "created_at": "2012-11-16T21:32:48Z", "updated_at": "2013-05-09T16:12:28Z", "closed_at": "2013-05-09T16:12:28Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "The following code fails to compile:\n\n```\nstruct HasNested {\n    mut nest: ~[~[int]],\n}\n\nimpl HasNested {\n\n    fn method_push_local() {\n        self.nest[0].push(0);\n    }\n\n}\n\nfn main() {}\n```\n\nThe rustc error message is:\n\n```\ntest-nested-mut-vec.rs:10:8: 10:19 error: illegal borrow unless pure: unique value in aliasable, mutable location\ntest-nested-mut-vec.rs:10         self.nest[0].push(0);\n                                  ^~~~~~~~~~~\ntest-nested-mut-vec.rs:10:8: 10:25 note: impure due to access to impure function\ntest-nested-mut-vec.rs:10         self.nest[0].push(0);\n                                  ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\nerror: aborting due to previous error\n```\n\nPCWalton and nikomatsakis suggested to me on IRC a few days ago that this should work. But right now I am not so sure - is the code bad because rustc thinks that vec.push might (via some alias) mutate self.nest thereby invalidating the pointer to self.nest[0] that it is passed? If this is the case then maybe the error message could be changed to make it clearer what the problem is.\n", "closed_by": {"login": "metajack", "id": 28357, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjI4MzU3", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/28357?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/metajack", "html_url": "https://github.com/metajack", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/metajack/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/metajack/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/metajack/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/metajack/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/metajack/subscriptio